Children in Scotland (Clann an Alba) is the national agency for voluntary, statutory and professional organisations and individuals working with children and their families. Established in 1983 as the Scottish Child and Family Alliance, it now has over 400 member organisations. It is a registered charity, based in Edinburgh.
It works in partnership with sister organisations National Childrenâ€™s Bureau (in England), Children in Wales and Children in Northern Ireland to form the 4 Nations Child Policy Network.
